name: Digas Colic Drops 20Ml
description: COMPOSITION : Each 2.5 ml Digas Colic Drop contains aqueous extract from dry herbs equivalent to : Fennel (Saunf) 50 mg, Mint (Podina Pahari) 40 mg, Mint (Podina desi) 40 mg, Cumin (Zeera Siah) 20 mg, Ginger (Sonth) 15 mg. Description : Digas Colic Drops are natural solution for relief of colic pain in babies. A mild, gentle and safe formulation of Fennel, Mint, Ginger and Cumin designed to relieve gas, bloating and abdominal pain.Colic upsets almost every baby to some degree and affects both breast-fed and bottle-fed babies. If your baby cries for three or more hours per day and at least three times per week it may be due to colic. Digas Colic Drops is a soothing combination of herbs popular through centuries for improving digestion and providing comfort in infant colic. description: The Folic Acid : Folic acid is also known as the vitamin B-9 is considered to be an all-rounder. It a synthetic type of folate which a naturally occurring B-vitamin that helps the body build healthy cells and turn food into energy. Folic acid is a busy vitamin considering it is used in dietary supplements and prenatal vitamins, and also get added up to packaged foods . Folic acid is a water soluble vitamin. Even though folic acid and folate are used as synonyms it is different in sense that it has a different structure than folate and has slightly different effects on the body. Benefits of Folic Acid : It helps in the growth of new tissues and cells. It builds proteins. It is known to break food down into nutrients . Folic acid is helpful in making red blood cells . It synthesizes and repairs the DNA. It prevents or treats anemia. It may improve heart health and reduce the risk of heart disease . Folic acid is the only type of folate that is proven to prevent neural tube defects. Folic acid for Pregnancy : Folic acid play an essential role in a babys development since it is involved in the cell division and tissue growth. Taking folic acid before and during pregnancy both is extremely beneficial since it can prevent neural tube irregularities and helps with babys brain and spine . Doctors and researches recommend anyone who is trying to get pregnant should start taking folic acid supplement containing 400-800 mcg at a month before getting pregnant and should continue taking it through first 2-3 months of pregnancy . Where does one get folic acid from?Folic acid can naturally be found in food such as spinach, nuts, kale, broccoli, avocado, citrus fruits, eggs, beef liver, and beans. It is also added to foods such as flour, ready-to-eat breakfast cereals, and breads. You can also find it in dietary supplements such as multivitamins, etc.

name: Ag-Cetam Injection 500Mg/5Ml
description: The mechanism of action of levetiracetam still remains to be fully elucidated. In vitro studies show that levetiracetam affects intraneuronal Ca2+ levels by partial inhibition of N- type Ca2+ currents and by reducing the release of Ca2+ from intraneuronal stores. In addition it partially reverses the reductions in GABA- and glycine-gated currents induced by zinc and -carbolines. Furthermore, levetiracetam has been shown in in vitro studies to bind to a specific site in rodent brain tissue. This binding site is the synaptic vesicle protein 2A, believed to be involved in vesicle fusion and neurotransmitter exocytosis. Levetiracetam and related analogs show a rank order of affinity for binding to the synaptic vesicle protein 2A which correlates with the potency of their anti-seizure protection in the mouse audiogenic model of epilepsy. This finding suggests that the interaction between levetiracetam and the synaptic vesicle protein 2A seems to contribute to the antiepileptic mechanism of action of the medicinal product.

name: Macushield Capsules (1 Box = 1 Strip)(1 Strip = 15 Capsules)
description: Generic : Lutein, Meso-Zeaxanthin, Zeaxanthin . Therapeutic Class : Eye Tonics & Eye Vitamins . Composition: Each Macushield capsule contains : Lutein: 10 mg , Meso-Zeaxanthin: 10 mg , Zeaxanthin: 2 mg . Description : MacuShield is the No.1 recommended supplement by eye experts (UK survey data of 92 eye experts). MacuShield is a lutein (10mg), meso-zeaxanthin (10mg) and zeaxanthin (2mg) once-a-day, easy to take, food supplement which combines all three macular carotenoids in a formula developed in collaboration with leading eye experts . Scientific research shows that these three nutrients are found at the back of the eye, at the macula, where they form the macular pigment (yellow colour).  The macular carotenoids in MacuShield are obtained from marigold (Tagetes Erecta), specifically grown for this purpose. Lutein is a natural carotenoid entirely of dietary origin, which accumulates at the macula at the back of the eye. Lutein is most commonly found in dark green, leafy vegetables such as spinach, kale or peas . Meso-zeaxanthin is the most central carotenoid found at the epicentre of the macula. Meso-zeaxanthin is naturally occurring in the human food chain, found in several species of fish to date. Zeaxanthin is a natural carotenoid entirely of dietary origin, which accumulates at the macula at the back of the eye. Zeaxanthin is commonly found in brightly coloured fruits and vegetables such as peppers and sweetcorn.Dosage: Take one MacuShield softgel capsule daily with meal.

description: Benefits : Helps to fulfil nutrient deficiency in the body ; Helps to maintain bone, joint and eye health ; Plays role in maintaining general health and wellbeing ; Supports strong immune system ; Provides antioxidant support and energy boost ; Helps to improve brain health and mental function. PRODUCT INFORMATION : Nutrifactors Multifactor is a dietary supplement with 22 essential vitamins and minerals, especially designed in proportion with the needs of elderly. It helps to strengthen the bones and muscles, maintain healthy vision, enhance immunity and improve cardiovascular as well as nervous system health. It also helps to reduce oxidative stress and fatigue. It includes Vitamin C which helps in improving iron absorption, Vitamin E that contributes to the protection of cells from oxidative stress, and Vitamin A which supports normal vision. Vitamin B1, B6, B12, Biotin and Vitamin C collectively, contribute to the maintenance of normal function of the nervous system, while Pantothenic Acid assists in normal mental performance. This comprehensive formula also includes Zinc which plays a key role in the maintenance of normal male hormone levels in the body and metabolism of fatty acids.DIRECTIONS : Take 1-2 tablets daily as a food supplement with meal or as directed by a healthcare professional. Do not exceed the recommended daily dose.

Magnesium deficiency may contribute to morning sickness during pregnancy. Iodine and Biotin deficiency may result in improper foetal development.  Recommended Daily Intake of Pregnazon Tablets: One Tablet daily with a main meal.  Pregnazon should only be taken on a full stomach.  Do not exceed recommended daily intake unless advised by a suitably qualified person. Caution: This product contains iron, which if taken in excess, may be harmful to very young children. Pregnazon Tablets are: Free from Dairy, Gelatine, Lactose, Yeast Soya, Nut .Free from Artificial Colours, Preservatives, and Flavourings . Suitable for Vegetarians and Vegans  .

name: Nutrifactor Qmint Cough Syrup 120Ml
description: Benefits : Helps relieve cough . Helps relieve throat irritation and chest congestion . Aids in clearing bronchial pathways by removing mucus . Helps restore normal breathing. Supports healthy lung function. Product Detail : Nutrifactors Qmint is a cough syrup containing traditional herbal extracts of Ivy leaf, Thyme & Licorice which are well known for their cough relieving and soothing properties. Ivy Leaf contains saponins which help in reducing the formation of viscous mucus in bronchi and overcoming shortness of breath and irritation of throat. Furthermore, its biological role includes a specific activity to control the metabolism of fats & sugar and cellular function of the nervous system. Myo-Inositol also recovers a regular menstrual cycle because of its modulatin action on the ovaries. Myo-Inositol is included into the protocols of controlled ovarian hyperstimulation. Folic acid: Folic acid plays an important role in metabolism of amino acids, synthesis of proteins and nucleic acid. It is an essential vitamin to take during pregnancy to prevents birth defects known as neural tube defacts. It is also used in anaemia due to folic acid deficiency.

description: Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm Indications : Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm is primarily indicated in conditions like Pediculosis, Scabies. Side Effects : The severe or irreversible adverse effects of Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm, which give rise to further complications include Insomnia, Paresthesia, Giddiness.Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm produces potentially life-threatening effects which include Seizures, Aplastic Anemia. Aplastic anemia. which are responsible for the discontinuation of Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm therapy.The signs and symptoms that are produced after the acute overdosage of Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm include Vomiting, Convulsions, Collapse, Restlessness, Muscular spasm, Loss of equilibrium. The symptomatic adverse reactions produced by Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm are more or less tolerable and if they become severe, they can be treated symptomatically, these include Dizziness, Headache, Nausea, Vomiting, Restlessness, Abdominal cramps, Confusion, Cough, Skin irritation, Contact dermatitis, Psoriasis, Confusion, dizziness, Contact dermatitis. Warnings : Lice-O-Nil Cream should not be used in patients with seizure disorders, have open wounds or sores or are allergic to Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm. Elderly persons may be more sensitive to the effects of this medication and a dose reduction may be required. Pregnant women should not be treated more than twice during the pregnancy. Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm should not be used in neonates, infants 2 years old and younger because of the possibility of high systemic absorption. Children 10 years old and younger also should be treated cautiously with Lice-O-Nil Cream 20 gm because of an increased potential for toxicity.

name: Misar-H Tablets 40/12.5Mg (1 Box = 2 Strips) (1 Strip = 10 Tablets)
description: Telmisartan :  Telmisartan is an orally effective and specific angiotensin II receptor subtype 1 (AT1) antagonist. Angiotensin II is formed from angiotensin I in a reaction catalyzed by angiotensinconverting enzyme (ACE, kininase II). Angiotensin II is the principal pressor agent of the renin-angiotensin system, with effects that include vasoconstriction, stimulation of synthesis and release of aldosterone, cardiac stimulation, and renal reabsorption of sodium. Telmisartan blocks the vasoconstrictor and aldosterone-secreting effects of angiotensin II by selectively blocking the binding of angiotensin II to the AT1 receptor in many tissues, such as vascular smooth muscle and the adrenal gland. Its action is therefore independent of the pathways for angiotensin II synthesis. In patients with hypertension telmisartan reduces both systolic and diastolic blood pressure without affecting pulse rate. Telmisartan has much greater affinity (>3,000 fold) for the AT1 receptor than for the AT2 receptor. Hydrochlorothiazide : Hydrochlorothiazide is a thiazide diuretic. Thiazides affect the renal tubular mechanisms of electrolyte reabsorption, directly increasing excretion of sodium and chloride in approximately equivalent amounts. The diuretic action of hydrochlorothiazide reduces plasma volume, increases plasma renin activity, increases aldosterone secretion, with consequent increases in urinary potassium and bicarbonate loss, and decreases in serum potassium. Presumably through blockade o f the renin-angiotensin-aldosterone system, co-administration of telmisartan tends to reverse the potassium loss associated with thiazide diuretics.

It is a dietary supplement and is used in the treatment of diabetic neuropathy, depression, Alzheimers disease, panic disorder and polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS).Emerging evidence shows promise for the use of myo-inositol in the reduction/prevention of gestational diabetes (GDM) in patients with PCOS or those at risk due to GDM or prior family history.It is classified as an insulin-sensitizing agent which acts to regulate a number of cellular functions including improved insulin utilization. It appears at least as effective as metformin, another insulin-sensitizing drug.In women with PCOS, myo-inositol improves insulin sensitivity and reduces insulin levels. Clinical studies have shown that myo-inositol may also : Decrease serum androgens (male hormones). Decrease triglycerides. Increase HDL cholesterol (the good cholesterol). Lower systolic and diastolic blood pressure.Folic acid : Folic acid is a water-soluble B vitamin. It is used for preventing and treating low blood levels of folate (folate deficiency), as well as anemia.Women who are pregnant or might become pregnant take folic acid to prevent miscarriage and neural tube defects.Momfolic plus sachet is used for good health of women of all age . It is indicated: To help promoting regular ovulation. To support regular menstrual cycle. To increase the quality of eggs released in each ovulation cycle. For Hirsutism, Obesity, PCOS, and Hyperinsulinemia.

name: Ag-Cetam Injection 500Mg/5Ml
description: The mechanism of action of levetiracetam still remains to be fully elucidated. In vitro studies show that levetiracetam affects intraneuronal Ca2+ levels by partial inhibition of N- type Ca2+ currents and by reducing the release of Ca2+ from intraneuronal stores. In addition it partially reverses the reductions in GABA- and glycine-gated currents induced by zinc and -carbolines. Furthermore, levetiracetam has been shown in in vitro studies to bind to a specific site in rodent brain tissue. This binding site is the synaptic vesicle protein 2A, believed to be involved in vesicle fusion and neurotransmitter exocytosis. Levetiracetam and related analogs show a rank order of affinity for binding to the synaptic vesicle protein 2A which correlates with the potency of their anti-seizure protection in the mouse audiogenic model of epilepsy. This finding suggests that the interaction between levetiracetam and the synaptic vesicle protein 2A seems to contribute to the antiepileptic mechanism of action of the medicinal product.

Dosage : AZVAC is formulated for use in adults only (12 years and older). Adults: Take one (1) tablet once a day with food. Exceeding the daily dose is not recommended. Nutritional supplements cannot replace a balanced diet. If you take more AZVAC than you should: In the event of over dosage, consult your doctor or pharmacist. If neither is available, seek help at the nearest hospital or poison control center. Possible Side Effects : AZVAC can have side effects. Not all side effects reported for AZVAC are included in this leaflet. Should your general health worsen while taking AZVAC, please consult your doctor, pharmacist or other healthcare professional for advice. Tell your doctor if you notice any of the following: Flushing of the skin, headaches, diarrhea, skin eruptions, sleeplessness, nervousness, hypertension, euphoria, swelling or a combination of itchy skin, joint aches and fever. If you notice any side effects not mentioned in this leaflet, please inform your doctor or pharmacist. Deficiencies may result in fatigue, malaise and lethargy. Thus, the requirement is linked to energy metabolism and will be increased by factors that increase the rate of energy utilization e.g. exercise. If neither is available, seek help at the nearest hospital or poison control center. Possible Side Effects : AZVAC can have side effects. Not all side effects reported for AZVAC are included in this leaflet. Should your general health worsen while taking AZVAC, please consult your doctor, pharmacist or other healthcare professional for advice. Tell your doctor if you notice any of the following: Flushing of the skin, headaches, diarrhea, skin eruptions, sleeplessness, nervousness, hypertension, euphoria, swelling or a combination of itchy skin, joint aches and fever. If you notice any side effects not mentioned in this leaflet, please inform your doctor or pharmacist. They play a well-known and critical role in the metabolic conversion of proteins, fats and carbohydrates to energy. B-vitamins are water-soluble and must be replaced daily. Deficiencies may result in fatigue, malaise and lethargy.
